<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-008-147 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 596 835</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Nov 25 1991 v13 n47 p71(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sonar Professional for Windows offers advantages over ZyIndex.andO;(Virginia Systems Software Services Inc search software) (SoftwareReview) (Windows Text Retrieval)(Test Drives) (Evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Marshall, Patrick.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Virginia Systems' Sonar Professional for Windows is a strong textretrieval package that offers clear advantages over competingproducts.andP;  The software lets users choose between the standardform of indexing and a form of index called 'Super Setup,' whichmakes searching virtually instantaneous.andP;  Unfortunately theprocess of doing a Super Setup takes as long as a regular indexprocedure, which is necessary first.andP;  A second drawback is thecomparatively large size of Sonar's index files.andP;  Sonar's searchcapabilities exceed even ZyIndex's tool set by offering phoneticsearches and searches for synonyms.andP;  Relational searching is alsosupported by a Sonar feature by which users specify a list ofterms and request that Sonar try to find relationships betweenthem in the users' databases.andP;  No price has been set, but theprobable cost is about $795.andP;  A version of Sonar that lacks manyof the frills of Sonar Professional will cost $295.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Virginia Systems Software Services Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Sonar Professional for Windows (Search software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationSearch SoftwareInformation storage and retrieval.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>